Why's the wheelchair here?

268
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:56,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)

269
00:25:57,500 --> 00:25:58,333
Shit.

270
00:26:06,083 --> 00:26:06,916
Hey!

271
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:18,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)
Shit!

272
00:26:24,708 --> 00:26:25,833
-Hey!
-It--

273
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:33,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)
What's the temperature?

274
00:26:47,958 --> 00:26:49,500
Unnatural, don't you think?

275
00:26:51,208 --> 00:26:53,916
This time,
we're one step closer to ghosts.

276
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:57,041
We witnessed energy
and temperature fluctuation.

277
00:26:58,500 --> 00:27:02,583
But our videos are no better than
those that have been shared online.

278
00:27:02,666 --> 00:27:04,375
Our evidence isn't solid yet.

279
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:06,833
I need to review my interviews.

280
00:27:07,625 --> 00:27:08,625
I may learn more.

281
00:27:09,250 --> 00:27:11,250
Gla, you can do it later, man.

282
00:27:24,250 --> 00:27:25,250
Dr. Gla.

283
00:27:26,083 --> 00:27:27,125
Are you alright?

284
00:27:51,958 --> 00:27:54,041
-Stop the bleeding.
-Apply pressure.

285
00:27:55,250 --> 00:27:57,500
Someone get Dr. Namo in here stat.

286
00:27:57,583 --> 00:27:58,875
Immediately, please!

287
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:05,125
You messed up
the tracheotomy. You nicked the thyroid.

288
00:28:05,208 --> 00:28:06,416
Do better, top student.

289
00:28:06,958 --> 00:28:09,708
Your late-night research is your business.

290
00:28:10,583 --> 00:28:11,708
But you should know

291
00:28:12,875 --> 00:28:14,583
that doctors' stupid mistakes

292
00:28:15,583 --> 00:28:16,750
cost patients' lives.

293
00:28:21,333 --> 00:28:22,166
Yes.

294
00:28:25,125 --> 00:28:26,958
Certainly. Thank you so much.

295
00:28:33,250 --> 00:28:34,083
Gla.

296
00:28:36,500 --> 00:28:38,833
-Hmm?
-I have bad news.

297
00:28:41,125 --> 00:28:42,000
Listen,

298
00:28:42,083 --> 00:28:43,250
in December,

299
00:28:44,791 --> 00:28:47,416
I have to oversee
a condo project in Pattaya.

300
00:28:49,708 --> 00:28:52,583
Can we postpone
our Northern Lights trip to, like,

301
00:28:54,125 --> 00:28:56,541
around next February?

302
00:28:57,916 --> 00:28:58,833
-Oh.
-Hmm?

303
00:29:00,250 --> 00:29:01,500
If that's convenient.

304
00:29:04,583 --> 00:29:05,916
Hey! Wait a minute.

305
00:29:07,291 --> 00:29:08,583
Are you being smooth?

306
00:29:11,708 --> 00:29:13,250
You forgot about our trip?

307
00:29:14,291 --> 00:29:16,000
I can tell. I know you.

308
00:29:20,666 --> 00:29:21,500
Sorry, babe.

309
00:29:23,083 --> 00:29:24,333
I hardly see you now.

310
00:29:28,125 --> 00:29:28,958
It's fine.

311
00:29:30,708 --> 00:29:33,083
When you're obsessed with work,

312
00:29:34,291 --> 00:29:35,708
it's so terribly sexy.

313
00:29:42,791 --> 00:29:43,666
I have to go.

314
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:46,833
Sure.

315
00:29:48,666 --> 00:29:49,500
I'm going now.

316
00:29:54,166 --> 00:29:56,000
-Bye-bye.
-Bye-bye, babe.

317
00:30:27,125 --> 00:30:32,666
FIND GHOSTS AS PARTICIPANTS,
APPEARANCE TRIGGER, PROOF

318
00:30:32,750 --> 00:30:35,458
Your platypus story gave me an idea.

319
00:30:35,958 --> 00:30:39,375
-Tell me, how do we classify animals?
-What? Why?

320
00:30:39,458 --> 00:30:40,708
How do we group them?

321
00:30:41,666 --> 00:30:42,750
We use criteria.

322
00:30:43,791 --> 00:30:45,125
Some are vertebrates.

323
00:30:45,208 --> 00:30:46,750
Some lay eggs. Some don't.

324
00:30:47,791 --> 00:30:51,166
-The number of legs varies.
-How might we classify ghosts?

325
00:30:55,416 --> 00:30:58,375
Have you noticed that when we saw ghosts,

326
00:30:58,458 --> 00:31:01,875
we knew some of them,
but some of them were strangers?

327
00:31:04,208 --> 00:31:05,666
-We knew some.
-Uh-huh.

328
00:31:06,250 --> 00:31:08,083
-Like my dad.
-That's right.

329
00:31:09,500 --> 00:31:11,916
The burn victim was a stranger to us.

330
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:13,083
KNOWN VS UNKNOWN

331
00:31:13,166 --> 00:31:14,041
Just think.

332
00:31:15,416 --> 00:31:16,291
Unknown ghosts.

333
00:31:17,166 --> 00:31:18,916
Why do they appear to us?

334
00:31:21,166 --> 00:31:25,166
-I don't know, man.
-Exactly. We don't know. It's dumb luck.

335
00:31:25,250 --> 00:31:26,875
Consider the known ghosts.

336
00:31:28,458 --> 00:31:30,708
Why did your dad's ghost come to you?

337
00:31:32,458 --> 00:31:34,875
Maybe he missed me or wanted to see me.

338
00:31:34,958 --> 00:31:36,750
If we focus on ghosts we know,

339
00:31:37,541 --> 00:31:40,625
we'll know where
and with whom to go find them.

340
00:31:40,708 --> 00:31:41,541
We could try

341
00:31:42,041 --> 00:31:45,708
observing someone
whose relative or lover has recently died.

342
00:31:46,291 --> 00:31:48,291
The only problem is…

343
00:31:50,875 --> 00:31:52,750
who'd let us do that all night?

344
00:31:52,833 --> 00:31:55,666
Especially if they know
we're researching ghosts!

345
00:31:58,083 --> 00:31:59,083
We can't do that.

346
00:32:00,541 --> 00:32:01,708
Here's another way.

347
00:32:03,458 --> 00:32:04,625
Don't be afraid.

348
00:32:05,958 --> 00:32:06,791
Alright?

349
00:32:14,541 --> 00:32:15,541
I know this girl,

350
00:32:17,125 --> 00:32:20,291
a first-year student who's
in the final stage of cancer.

351
00:32:21,125 --> 00:32:22,375
I heard she's single.

352
00:32:23,750 --> 00:32:24,583
Imagine that.

353
00:32:25,250 --> 00:32:27,291
She's never dated and she's dying.

354
00:32:28,541 --> 00:32:30,083
But if you or I

355
00:32:30,166 --> 00:32:33,166
become her first and only boyfriend,

356
00:32:34,083 --> 00:32:36,833
when she's gone,
she'll surely come back to us.

357
00:32:40,375 --> 00:32:41,791
Are we going too far?

358
00:32:42,416 --> 00:32:45,125
Fooling a dying person for our experiment?

359
00:32:45,208 --> 00:32:47,250
I think we'd be crossing the line.

360
00:32:50,333 --> 00:32:51,416
So what?

361
00:32:52,583 --> 00:32:56,416
She gets some love
before she dies. We get a participant. So,

362
00:32:56,500 --> 00:32:58,208
win-win, right? Wee?

363
00:32:59,708 --> 00:33:01,916
That feeling when we saw the ghost…

364
00:33:04,583 --> 00:33:07,541
The universe opened
its door of secrets to us.

365
00:33:09,833 --> 00:33:11,583
My curiosity's unstoppable now.

366
00:33:20,875 --> 00:33:21,708
Hello?

367
00:33:25,208 --> 00:33:26,083
What?

368
00:33:35,625 --> 00:33:39,166
The brain can survive
without oxygen for three minutes.

369
00:33:39,250 --> 00:33:43,041
The brain can survive
without oxygen for three minutes…

370
00:33:43,125 --> 00:33:44,250
I resuscitated her.

371
00:33:44,875 --> 00:33:46,375
She's still unresponsive.

372
00:33:47,750 --> 00:33:50,666
Mucus blocked
her airway awhile before we arrived.

373
00:33:51,625 --> 00:33:55,458
No oxygen reached her brain
for seven minutes. You have to choose.

374
00:34:01,583 --> 00:34:02,583
-Hey!
-Hey, Wee!

375
00:34:17,583 --> 00:34:18,416
Mom…

376
00:34:20,666 --> 00:34:21,625
do you remember…

377
00:34:24,541 --> 00:34:27,166
the robot you bought me when I was a kid?

378
00:34:30,041 --> 00:34:35,083
One day, I threw it a bit too hard,
and after that, it couldn't walk anymore.

379
00:34:36,500 --> 00:34:37,791
Back then, you said

380
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:40,333
that it couldn't walk…

381
00:34:43,833 --> 00:34:45,750
because it was broken inside…

382
00:34:47,833 --> 00:34:49,458
and we'd be able to fix it.

383
00:34:57,916 --> 00:34:58,791
But…

384
00:35:02,875 --> 00:35:04,583
I know what's wrong with you,

385
00:35:09,416 --> 00:35:11,416
so why can't I help you at all?

386
00:35:25,708 --> 00:35:26,666
So you're sure

387
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:29,291
the afterlife's real?

388
00:35:36,208 --> 00:35:37,875
Do you want to go now, Mom?

389
00:35:41,041 --> 00:35:42,875
Am I torturing you here?

390
00:35:49,458 --> 00:35:50,291
I believe

391
00:35:51,375 --> 00:35:52,291
that it's real.

392
00:36:11,750 --> 00:36:13,000
I'll let you go, Mom.

393
00:36:16,458 --> 00:36:18,083
Please come back to see me.

394
00:36:54,541 --> 00:36:56,458
There's no new patient here yet,

395
00:36:57,541 --> 00:36:58,916
so I installed a camera

396
00:36:59,708 --> 00:37:01,541
to capture any weird movements.

397
00:37:05,666 --> 00:37:06,500
And tonight,

398
00:37:08,125 --> 00:37:10,125
I think I should be by Wee's side.

399
00:38:30,958 --> 00:38:32,083
Mom?

400
00:38:50,125 --> 00:38:50,958
Mom!

401
00:39:16,166 --> 00:39:19,666
Mom seemed to be saying
something, but I couldn't tell what.

402
00:39:25,416 --> 00:39:26,500
I saw her crying.

403
00:39:31,250 --> 00:39:32,916
Did I make the wrong choice?

404
00:39:38,500 --> 00:39:39,583
Maybe the truth is

405
00:39:41,041 --> 00:39:43,000
she didn't want me to let her go.

406
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:55,916
After that day,

407
00:39:57,083 --> 00:39:58,916
Mom never let me see her again.

408
00:40:04,375 --> 00:40:06,500
I have so many questions in my head,

409
00:40:08,416 --> 00:40:09,958
I feel like I'm drowning.

410
00:40:16,916 --> 00:40:22,208
So I decided to do PHQ-9, fMRI,
as well as blood and urine lab tests

411
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:24,625
for chemical imbalances.

412
00:40:27,500 --> 00:40:28,666
We found nothing.

413
00:40:40,458 --> 00:40:41,500
That means

414
00:40:42,125 --> 00:40:44,958
I'm not depressed
because of what happened.

415
00:41:58,583 --> 00:42:00,166
Therefore, my decision

416
00:42:01,750 --> 00:42:03,750
isn't influenced by anything else.

417
00:42:17,750 --> 00:42:18,916
I will cross over.

418
00:42:23,375 --> 00:42:25,916
"Cross over"? To where?

419
00:42:28,791 --> 00:42:31,208
I'll die and go to the other side,

420
00:42:32,416 --> 00:42:35,541
and I'll come back
to do the experiment with you.

421
00:42:36,458 --> 00:42:37,708
Dude. Chill, man.

422
00:42:37,791 --> 00:42:41,333
It's what we need
for our experiment to continue.

423
00:42:42,625 --> 00:42:45,333
Even if the cancer patient fell for you,

424
00:42:45,416 --> 00:42:46,875
even if she came to you,

425
00:42:46,958 --> 00:42:49,291
how much could you experiment with her?

426
00:42:50,250 --> 00:42:53,041
She could disappear
in an instant like your dad.

427
00:42:54,166 --> 00:42:58,291
She doesn't know our experiment
like us or understand what we're doing.

428
00:42:58,375 --> 00:43:00,750
Only I can come back for our experiment.

429
00:43:00,833 --> 00:43:01,833
Snap out of it.

430
00:43:03,750 --> 00:43:05,416
You're upset about your mom.

431
00:43:06,500 --> 00:43:09,083
You're just depressed, so you're suicidal.

432
00:43:09,958 --> 00:43:12,166
Wee, listen to me, damn it.

433
00:43:15,041 --> 00:43:16,250
You lost your mom,

434
00:43:16,833 --> 00:43:18,666
but you didn't lose everything.

435
00:43:19,291 --> 00:43:21,791
-You still have so much to do.
-Like what?

436
00:43:24,083 --> 00:43:24,916
Huh?

437
00:43:26,708 --> 00:43:27,833
What's left to do?

438
00:43:29,958 --> 00:43:31,083
Why care if I die?

439
00:43:31,166 --> 00:43:32,041
You're my friend!

440
00:43:32,125 --> 00:43:33,666
And you're my friend too.

441
00:43:35,000 --> 00:43:36,541
I'm doing your experiment.

442
00:43:38,291 --> 00:43:40,250
Since we saw that ghost together,

443
00:43:41,916 --> 00:43:43,791
and my mom came back to see me,

444
00:43:43,875 --> 00:43:46,250
I'm not afraid of the afterlife anymore.

445
00:43:48,083 --> 00:43:49,041
In this world,

446
00:43:49,583 --> 00:43:52,083
there's no one left for me to worry about.

447
00:43:57,250 --> 00:43:58,833
I just want to see my mom.

448
00:44:02,541 --> 00:44:04,166
I wanna know what she said.

449
00:44:09,416 --> 00:44:10,958
You're the one who told me

450
00:44:12,291 --> 00:44:15,208
"the universe has opened
its door of secrets to us"

451
00:44:15,291 --> 00:44:16,958
and you expect me to do nothing?

452
00:44:19,291 --> 00:44:20,625
It's not unusual, Gla.

453
00:44:22,166 --> 00:44:25,541
Lots of scientists trade
their lives for discoveries.

454
00:44:26,041 --> 00:44:27,416
Didn't you say so yourself?

455
00:44:28,416 --> 00:44:30,208
That you were born to do this?

456
00:44:32,958 --> 00:44:35,791
This is it! This is how you prove it!

457
00:44:35,875 --> 00:44:38,083
You don't understand shit!

458
00:44:38,916 --> 00:44:40,333
I got you into this!

459
00:44:41,375 --> 00:44:42,958
How can I let you die?

460
00:44:45,166 --> 00:44:46,083
Think it through.

461
00:44:47,250 --> 00:44:49,125
I can't let you die for this!

462
00:44:49,208 --> 00:44:50,291
Don't stop me!

463
00:44:52,333 --> 00:44:55,166
You'll get a participant.
I'll get to see my mom.

464
00:44:56,291 --> 00:44:57,125
Win-win, yeah?

465
00:45:15,958 --> 00:45:16,958
Just admit it.

466
00:45:20,000 --> 00:45:23,625
This is the only way
our experiment can continue.

467
00:45:35,583 --> 00:45:36,791
If someone must die,

468
00:45:38,791 --> 00:45:39,750
it will be me.

469
00:45:43,208 --> 00:45:44,208
What the hell?

470
00:45:48,375 --> 00:45:49,375
Fine, I admit it.

471
00:45:51,125 --> 00:45:52,333
Yeah, you're right.

472
00:45:52,416 --> 00:45:54,625
This is the only way we can continue.

473
00:45:56,875 --> 00:45:58,500
But I started this project.

474
00:45:59,166 --> 00:46:03,166
-This crucial task should be mine!
-You're talking shit. I volunteer!

475
00:46:03,250 --> 00:46:04,666
I volunteer too!

476
00:46:06,541 --> 00:46:07,375
I will die

477
00:46:08,458 --> 00:46:10,083
for the research I started.

478
00:46:10,166 --> 00:46:11,500
I have that right too!

479
00:46:23,625 --> 00:46:24,958
So let's make it fair.

480
00:46:36,166 --> 00:46:37,000
If it's heads,

481
00:46:38,125 --> 00:46:38,958
I'll go.

482
00:46:40,125 --> 00:46:40,958
If it's tails,

483
00:46:42,833 --> 00:46:43,666
you'll go.

484
00:46:51,000 --> 00:46:52,375
Whatever the result is,

485
00:46:54,000 --> 00:46:55,000
you'll accept it.

486
00:47:59,791 --> 00:48:01,041
I thought it through.

487
00:48:04,833 --> 00:48:06,583
I'll write a suicide note.

488
00:48:07,500 --> 00:48:08,916
I'll say I got depressed

489
00:48:09,541 --> 00:48:10,625
after my mom died.

490
00:48:11,416 --> 00:48:13,708
You'll just pretend you found my body.

491
00:48:14,916 --> 00:48:17,791
Forensics will say
that I killed myself for sure.

492
00:48:19,750 --> 00:48:21,625
Just keep our experiment secret

493
00:48:22,375 --> 00:48:24,083
so the cops won't bother us.

494
00:48:30,666 --> 00:48:34,458
I'll wait on the other side to see
our names on that front cover.

495
00:48:37,041 --> 00:48:38,791
A free solo mountain climber,

496
00:48:38,875 --> 00:48:42,500
or a climber who uses
bare hands and no cables or safety gear,

497
00:48:42,583 --> 00:48:44,541
has fatally fallen off a cliff

498
00:48:44,625 --> 00:48:46,458
attempting to set a new record

499
00:48:46,541 --> 00:48:48,833
by climbing at Yosemite National Park

500
00:48:48,916 --> 00:48:51,125
in the US state of California.

501
00:48:51,208 --> 00:48:52,958
Why do people do this stuff?

502
00:48:54,375 --> 00:48:55,625
What do they get from it?

503
00:48:57,375 --> 00:48:58,541
Is it worth dying for?

504
00:49:10,958 --> 00:49:13,041
Experiment log number 65,

505
00:49:14,750 --> 00:49:16,833
23rd August, 2019.

506
00:49:20,333 --> 00:49:21,833
Every life has an ending.

507
00:49:24,041 --> 00:49:26,875
But what
are we going to use that ending for?

508
00:49:28,750 --> 00:49:30,166
True science

509
00:49:31,250 --> 00:49:33,166
is the journey from ignorance

510
00:49:33,708 --> 00:49:34,541
to knowledge,

511
00:49:35,458 --> 00:49:38,208
from stupidity to wisdom,

512
00:49:39,291 --> 00:49:42,208
from mystery to enlightenment.

513
00:49:44,541 --> 00:49:46,291
My journey today

514
00:49:47,625 --> 00:49:50,458
will bring us closer to
the truth of the universe.

515
00:49:51,875 --> 00:49:53,625
This video clip will record

516
00:49:54,875 --> 00:49:58,208
my entire journey to the other side.

517
00:50:00,583 --> 00:50:02,416
Dr. Arjong Soonyata

518
00:50:04,083 --> 00:50:06,750
will conduct the research on this side.

519
00:50:07,708 --> 00:50:09,166
If I don't return soon,

520
00:50:11,125 --> 00:50:13,291
Dr. Ar-Jong may have to work harder.

521
00:50:19,208 --> 00:50:20,083
I think

522
00:50:20,916 --> 00:50:21,791
it's time

523
00:50:23,583 --> 00:50:25,375
for us to begin our journey.

524
00:50:50,583 --> 00:50:52,833
I don't know what it'll be like there.

525
00:50:53,500 --> 00:50:56,416
But I will do everything
to make contact with you.

526
00:50:58,166 --> 00:51:01,916
And you have to do
everything you can to contact me too.

527
00:51:02,000 --> 00:51:03,208
I swear I will, man.

528
00:51:04,750 --> 00:51:06,666
I won't stop until you get back,

529
00:51:07,666 --> 00:51:08,708
until we succeed.

530
00:51:43,708 --> 00:51:44,916
Shit!

531
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:36,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)
I was born to prove ghosts are real.

532
00:52:38,708 --> 00:52:40,333
I'm in.

533
00:52:40,416 --> 00:52:44,333
Our work must be published
in the most famous research journal.

534
00:52:46,291 --> 00:52:49,833
I'll wait on the other side to see
our names on that front cover.

535
00:52:51,125 --> 00:52:52,625
Come back to me, Mom.

536
00:52:57,125 --> 00:52:59,000
What are you two doing, honey?

537
00:53:12,833 --> 00:53:13,666
Mom!

538
00:53:37,208 --> 00:53:38,125
I can't do it.

539
00:53:39,125 --> 00:53:40,875
I really can't. My mom, she…

540
00:53:42,791 --> 00:53:45,000
I'm sorry.

541
00:53:53,083 --> 00:53:54,125
It's OK, man.

542
00:53:55,416 --> 00:53:56,333
I'll come back.

543
00:54:29,708 --> 00:54:32,000
-Doctor, it's your cue.
-Alright.

544
00:54:32,500 --> 00:54:36,291
Have you ever proven
that your beliefs aren't just nonsense

545
00:54:36,375 --> 00:54:37,875
or just superstitions?

546
00:54:37,958 --> 00:54:38,833
Ready?

547
00:54:38,916 --> 00:54:41,625
I'd like you all to meet
two important people

548
00:54:42,250 --> 00:54:45,083
who will change your beliefs forever.

549
00:54:59,958 --> 00:55:01,875
Do you believe in the afterlife?

550
00:55:02,458 --> 00:55:05,041
And spirits? What do you think they are?

551
00:55:05,125 --> 00:55:06,666
I, Dr. Cheewee Prometheus,

552
00:55:06,750 --> 00:55:08,500
and Dr. Arjong Soonyata,

553
00:55:08,583 --> 00:55:10,291
our key research participant,

554
00:55:10,375 --> 00:55:12,666
are standing side by side right now.

555
00:55:12,750 --> 00:55:17,000
We'll now present our results
as seen in the world-class journal,

556
00:55:17,083 --> 00:55:18,041
The Experiment.

557
00:55:18,125 --> 00:55:20,750
You are the first group to witness this.

558
00:55:22,333 --> 00:55:23,166
Are you ready,

559
00:55:23,958 --> 00:55:24,791
Dr. Ar-Jong?

560
00:55:37,541 --> 00:55:38,500
It doesn't work!

561
00:55:39,166 --> 00:55:40,250
Dr. Cheewee,

562
00:55:40,791 --> 00:55:44,333
I'm happy for… your success.

563
00:55:44,958 --> 00:55:48,041
But for this discovery,
which you say is so amazing,

564
00:55:48,125 --> 00:55:51,333
were you really willing
to sacrifice a person's life?

565
00:55:57,375 --> 00:55:58,875
Do you even have a heart?

566
00:56:00,958 --> 00:56:02,750
You let your friend kill himself

567
00:56:02,833 --> 00:56:05,541
for an experiment
you don't know will succeed or not.

568
00:56:06,166 --> 00:56:09,750
You're not the researcher
or scientist you think you are.

569
00:56:09,833 --> 00:56:13,875
You're a murderer.

570
00:56:17,708 --> 00:56:18,541
Mai.

571
00:56:22,666 --> 00:56:23,625
Hey. No!

572
00:57:01,458 --> 00:57:04,750
NO CONTACT

573
00:57:08,041 --> 00:57:09,541
ON-CALL ROOM SUICIDE!

574
00:57:09,625 --> 00:57:11,041
WHY DID DOC SHOOT SELF?

575
00:57:11,125 --> 00:57:13,250
DOC KILLS SELF IN HAUNTED HOSPITAL!

576
00:57:13,333 --> 00:57:14,958
TRAGIC DOC'S MOTIVE UNKNOWN

577
00:57:27,250 --> 00:57:28,791
I tried everything I could

578
00:57:30,125 --> 00:57:31,500
to stop Wee's thoughts.

579
00:57:39,958 --> 00:57:41,750
I never thought of this method.

580
00:57:43,875 --> 00:57:46,875
But once he said it,
my heart started beating hard.

581
00:57:49,208 --> 00:57:50,041
I felt…

582
00:57:51,666 --> 00:57:52,500
Damn!

583
00:57:54,375 --> 00:57:56,291
Is this the solution we seek?

584
00:58:04,375 --> 00:58:05,291
I'll come back.

585
00:58:15,916 --> 00:58:16,750
I'm sorry.

586
00:58:24,750 --> 00:58:25,791
Come back now.

587
00:58:29,125 --> 00:58:33,250
Gla donated his body
to the hospital for educational purposes…

588
00:58:33,333 --> 00:58:34,291
DR. ARJONG

589
00:58:34,375 --> 00:58:35,958
…to benefit others.

590
00:58:37,541 --> 00:58:38,750
But the monk said

591
00:58:39,791 --> 00:58:41,791
that suicide is a grave sin.

592
00:58:43,750 --> 00:58:46,958
I'm doing everything
to make him pure like anyone else.

593
00:58:49,166 --> 00:58:50,583
Wee, do you think

594
00:58:52,208 --> 00:58:53,208
what I'm doing

595
00:58:55,375 --> 00:58:57,833
will help Gla find peace, sweetheart?

596
00:59:11,125 --> 00:59:12,208
Thank you, Wee.

597
00:59:13,916 --> 00:59:15,625
I'll bring it all to his mom.

598
00:59:18,583 --> 00:59:20,791
Could you think it over again?

599
00:59:22,750 --> 00:59:24,916
Why would Gla do this?

600
00:59:28,500 --> 00:59:29,791
I really don't know.

601
00:59:32,041 --> 00:59:32,875
I'm sorry.

602
00:59:51,708 --> 00:59:52,916
Not knowing anything

603
00:59:54,875 --> 00:59:56,208
really freaking hurts.

604
00:59:59,875 --> 01:00:01,833
It's like I meant nothing to him.

605
01:00:54,458 --> 01:00:55,333
Shit!

606
01:02:19,291 --> 01:02:20,416
Whoa! Shit!

607
01:02:32,041 --> 01:02:32,875
Jackass!

608
01:02:34,250 --> 01:02:35,500
You're back, asshole?

609
01:02:40,958 --> 01:02:41,916
It's you, right?

610
01:02:46,291 --> 01:02:47,125
Gla!

611
01:02:49,791 --> 01:02:50,625
Gla?

612
01:02:57,166 --> 01:02:58,166
You're here?

613
01:02:58,250 --> 01:03:00,041
You're back? Why can't I see you?

614
01:03:00,125 --> 01:03:02,166
Why don't you show yourself to me?

615
01:03:07,916 --> 01:03:10,791
Maybe… you can't show yourself yet.

616
01:03:12,708 --> 01:03:13,541
Communicate.

617
01:03:14,208 --> 01:03:15,208
Make sounds. Or--

618
01:03:15,750 --> 01:03:17,333
Or do whatever you can.

619
01:03:17,416 --> 01:03:18,958
Do your poltergeist shit.

620
01:03:59,250 --> 01:04:01,833
Hey… you're communicating with me, right?

621
01:04:04,291 --> 01:04:06,125
Why can't you communicate more?

622
01:04:08,708 --> 01:04:11,000
I was falling and you pulled me back!

623
01:04:19,916 --> 01:04:20,791
Hold on.

624
01:04:22,875 --> 01:04:24,833
You saved me when I was falling?

625
01:04:29,416 --> 01:04:30,333
Let me guess.

626
01:04:30,416 --> 01:04:32,166
What boosts your power

627
01:04:33,041 --> 01:04:34,958
is me being in danger, right?

628
01:04:36,458 --> 01:04:38,416
If I put myself at risk again,

629
01:04:38,500 --> 01:04:40,750
will it boost your energy again?

630
01:05:15,291 --> 01:05:16,208
I'm a surgeon.

631
01:05:19,291 --> 01:05:20,416
Save my finger, OK?

632
01:05:22,916 --> 01:05:23,750
Dr. Wee?

633
01:05:25,166 --> 01:05:26,000
Shit.

634
01:05:26,833 --> 01:05:30,250
Please sign the schedule.
I called but you didn't pick up.

635
01:05:34,333 --> 01:05:35,166
Alright.

636
01:05:50,375 --> 01:05:51,208
Shit!

637
01:06:03,791 --> 01:06:05,291
Is my hypothesis correct?

638
01:06:05,375 --> 01:06:06,416
Is my idea right?

639
01:06:24,583 --> 01:06:25,625
Ghost participant

640
01:06:26,250 --> 01:06:28,166
found. You're back.

641
01:06:28,916 --> 01:06:31,541
Next, we need to find
a way for you to appear.

642
01:06:32,291 --> 01:06:34,750
So do you know what ghosts are now?

643
01:06:37,416 --> 01:06:40,958
Gla's return doesn't answer
all the questions we're asking,

644
01:06:41,041 --> 01:06:42,458
but we've learned a lot.

645
01:06:43,083 --> 01:06:45,916
First of all, Gla can't see other ghosts.

646
01:06:46,000 --> 01:06:49,125
How about there? Can you see anything?

647
01:06:50,625 --> 01:06:51,791
Secondly,

648
01:06:51,875 --> 01:06:53,666
he only sees what's around me.

649
01:06:54,833 --> 01:06:57,500
He says that before this, he saw nothing,

650
01:06:58,916 --> 01:07:00,250
until I jumped.

651
01:07:03,041 --> 01:07:05,416
Suddenly, he saw me and saved me.

652
01:07:06,333 --> 01:07:11,666
It's like something connects
me to Gla, who's in the afterlife.

653
01:07:13,250 --> 01:07:15,458
That means the soul's power increases

654
01:07:16,041 --> 01:07:17,750
when triggered by something.

655
01:07:21,416 --> 01:07:24,708
In our case,
Gla was worried about me being in danger.

656
01:07:26,500 --> 01:07:29,041
Let's say ghosts are natural phenomena.

657
01:07:29,125 --> 01:07:30,750
If ghosts are like wind…

658
01:07:30,833 --> 01:07:33,166
Wind, initially, can't be seen, right?

659
01:07:33,708 --> 01:07:36,541
But add air pressure
to wind and you get a storm,

660
01:07:37,791 --> 01:07:40,958
which can increase in both speed and size.

661
01:07:41,041 --> 01:07:42,416
And then,

662
01:07:43,416 --> 01:07:45,375
when that mixes with water vapor,

663
01:07:46,500 --> 01:07:48,708
it creates an electric charge. Finally,

664
01:07:48,791 --> 01:07:49,625
we will see…

665
01:07:54,291 --> 01:07:57,375
the shape of an actual storm. I believe

666
01:07:57,916 --> 01:08:00,666
that if I can boost your power like this,

667
01:08:01,541 --> 01:08:04,000
you'll be able to appear for sure, man.

668
01:08:08,791 --> 01:08:12,208
"Weird"? How are my thoughts weird?

669
01:08:16,916 --> 01:08:17,750
"Beach"?

670
01:08:20,750 --> 01:08:22,458
No beach pictures in here.

671
01:08:23,375 --> 01:08:24,916
Where do you see a beach?

672
01:08:30,458 --> 01:08:31,291
Gone already?

673
01:08:37,916 --> 01:08:41,083
W-- What stupid beach
are you talking about?

674
01:08:53,375 --> 01:08:54,208
Aunt Koy?

675
01:08:54,708 --> 01:08:55,583
This picture…

676
01:08:56,666 --> 01:08:57,708
Where was this?

677
01:08:58,458 --> 01:09:00,583
Oh, that was taken in Ranong.

678
01:09:01,791 --> 01:09:03,041
It's Gla's hometown.

679
01:09:04,250 --> 01:09:07,416
When his dad passed away,
I moved back to Bangkok.

680
01:09:15,750 --> 01:09:17,916
You said you wanted to talk to me

681
01:09:19,083 --> 01:09:19,916
about Gla.

682
01:09:22,916 --> 01:09:23,750
What is it?

683
01:09:30,291 --> 01:09:31,125
Well…

684
01:09:36,708 --> 01:09:37,958
I saw Gla in a dream.

685
01:09:43,083 --> 01:09:45,041
He told me to tell you something.

686
01:09:47,041 --> 01:09:47,875
He said…

687
01:09:50,625 --> 01:09:51,791
he's still around.

688
01:09:56,250 --> 01:09:57,666
He can't be reborn yet.

689
01:09:59,791 --> 01:10:01,041
What do I need to do?

690
01:10:02,666 --> 01:10:03,916
Did he tell you?

691
01:10:08,333 --> 01:10:10,625
I guess suicide is a very serious sin.

692
01:10:12,583 --> 01:10:16,208
I'm afraid that he's going to
carry on as a wandering ghost.

693
01:10:30,375 --> 01:10:31,375
I got goosebumps.

694
01:10:33,041 --> 01:10:34,458
Wee, do you feel it too?

695
01:10:35,875 --> 01:10:38,416
-I do.
-Maybe Gla is here somewhere.

696
01:10:42,375 --> 01:10:43,208
Mom.

697
01:10:47,708 --> 01:10:48,833
Excuse me, Wee.

698
01:10:49,458 --> 01:10:52,208
What you're saying is upsetting my mom.

699
01:10:53,666 --> 01:10:57,416
Plus, you're a doctor. You aren't
supposed to believe in this stuff?

700
01:11:00,333 --> 01:11:01,833
I'm just worried for Gla.

701
01:11:04,875 --> 01:11:05,833
What you said…

702
01:11:07,916 --> 01:11:09,666
don't you think it hurts Gla?

703
01:11:11,375 --> 01:11:13,291
He might be here with us now.

704
01:11:13,375 --> 01:11:14,708
That's nonsense.

705
01:11:17,625 --> 01:11:19,541
You're only hurting my mom more.

706
01:11:19,625 --> 01:11:20,625
You should leave.

707
01:11:21,333 --> 01:11:22,166
Please go.

708
01:11:23,083 --> 01:11:25,041
-Gift.
-Hush, Mom.

709
01:11:40,041 --> 01:11:41,000
"Kha Kai."

710
01:11:52,916 --> 01:11:54,041
I just remembered.

711
01:11:55,875 --> 01:11:57,916
In my dream, Gla said, "Kha Kai."

712
01:11:58,000 --> 01:11:58,916
"Chicken legs"?

713
01:11:59,625 --> 01:12:00,916
I don't get it either,

714
01:12:01,000 --> 01:12:02,791
but he really said, "Kha Kai."

715
01:12:08,416 --> 01:12:09,250
Wee.

716
01:12:11,625 --> 01:12:12,958
Do stay for dinner.

717
01:12:18,916 --> 01:12:21,291
Gla loved my Kha Kai curry.

718
01:12:24,416 --> 01:12:25,250
Oh.

719
01:12:27,083 --> 01:12:28,000
He meant curry.

720
01:12:29,500 --> 01:12:31,875
He must want me to offer alms for him,

721
01:12:32,583 --> 01:12:33,583
so he told you.

722
01:12:38,166 --> 01:12:39,000
Whoa.

723
01:12:41,250 --> 01:12:43,666
Wow. Your cooking is amazing, Aunt Koy.

724
01:12:44,250 --> 01:12:46,333
You could open your own restaurant.

725
01:12:53,166 --> 01:12:54,833
That's what Gla said too.

726
01:12:57,083 --> 01:12:58,333
Gla complimented me.

727
01:12:58,416 --> 01:13:00,166
He said my curry was so good

728
01:13:00,791 --> 01:13:02,500
that I could run a restaurant.

729
01:13:04,375 --> 01:13:05,541
I didn't buy that.

730
01:13:05,625 --> 01:13:08,958
So he dared me. He said
he'd have you come to taste it.

731
01:13:20,208 --> 01:13:22,041
He said you'd say the same thing.

732
01:13:27,000 --> 01:13:28,916
Gla said that I'm not confident…

733
01:13:32,416 --> 01:13:34,666
that I think I'm not good at anything.

734
01:13:40,250 --> 01:13:41,083
He said, "But

735
01:13:42,625 --> 01:13:43,583
if that's true,

736
01:13:44,625 --> 01:13:46,958
how did you raise your kids alone?"

737
01:13:50,750 --> 01:13:53,083
He said, "You raised a doctor, right?"

738
01:13:55,500 --> 01:13:57,833
"Compared to that, Kha Kai is so easy."

739
01:13:59,250 --> 01:14:01,833
"Why won't you believe
you're a great cook?"

740
01:14:09,791 --> 01:14:11,000
Thank you, Wee.

741
01:14:13,625 --> 01:14:17,250
Now I understand
what Gla wanted to tell me.

742
01:14:40,958 --> 01:14:42,916
The curry brought your mom peace.

743
01:14:43,708 --> 01:14:46,083
Did you derail my experiment on purpose?

744
01:14:52,750 --> 01:14:54,208
You know the plan.

745
01:14:54,291 --> 01:14:58,125
I'm trying to make you worry
as much as I can. It worked, see?

746
01:15:08,541 --> 01:15:09,500
I understand

747
01:15:10,500 --> 01:15:12,416
if you don't like me doing this.

748
01:15:14,666 --> 01:15:16,583
But it's for the experiment.

749
01:15:22,416 --> 01:15:23,250
Right now?

750
01:15:30,750 --> 01:15:34,250
So is this the beach
in Ranong, your hometown?

751
01:15:37,666 --> 01:15:38,500
Hey, Gla!

752
01:15:39,333 --> 01:15:40,875
Gla! Hey!

753
01:15:42,625 --> 01:15:43,458
Damn it, Gla!

754
01:15:47,333 --> 01:15:49,458
Gla has been missing for three days.

755
01:15:51,625 --> 01:15:52,750
Is this normal?

756
01:15:54,291 --> 01:15:56,791
Does every spirit have this phase?

757
01:15:58,666 --> 01:16:02,166
Or maybe he left
because he's consoled his mom.

758
01:16:02,250 --> 01:16:04,166
WORLD OF THE LIVING

759
01:16:04,250 --> 01:16:07,833
GLA

760
01:16:07,916 --> 01:16:09,625
Or is the beach another world

761
01:16:10,208 --> 01:16:13,125
the dead have to
cross to, like how some folks say

762
01:16:14,000 --> 01:16:15,666
"the dead go to find peace."

763
01:16:41,250 --> 01:16:42,083
Come back.

764
01:16:46,916 --> 01:16:47,750
Three…

765
01:16:51,541 --> 01:16:52,416
two…

766
01:16:56,125 --> 01:16:57,000
one!

767
01:17:13,208 --> 01:17:15,625
Wee. If you have any problems

768
01:17:15,708 --> 01:17:17,500
or stress, you can tell me.

769
01:17:19,250 --> 01:17:20,125
Or the hospital

770
01:17:20,208 --> 01:17:21,833
has professionals who can help--

771
01:17:21,916 --> 01:17:22,958
Meaning what?

772
01:17:25,666 --> 01:17:28,666
A nurse says you tried
this once before. Is it true?

773
01:17:32,666 --> 01:17:34,041
Who maims themselves?

774
01:17:38,500 --> 01:17:41,666
-So is it true?
-I can handle it. I don't need help.

775
01:17:52,541 --> 01:17:53,375
Shit.

776
01:17:57,041 --> 01:17:57,875
Oh, hi, Mai.

777
01:18:02,083 --> 01:18:03,375
Why are you here?

778
01:18:04,916 --> 01:18:06,000
I came to see you

779
01:18:07,083 --> 01:18:08,125
to ask you this.

780
01:18:08,791 --> 01:18:10,833
The day I returned Gla's stuff,

781
01:18:11,625 --> 01:18:13,166
his laptop was missing.

782
01:18:13,250 --> 01:18:14,875
The one with the red cover.

783
01:18:15,583 --> 01:18:19,083
It's not at his mom's place
and the cops didn't take it.

784
01:18:19,916 --> 01:18:21,125
Have you seen it?

785
01:18:24,625 --> 01:18:25,458
I haven't.

786
01:18:27,916 --> 01:18:30,666
I'll look for it and let you know ASAP.

787
01:18:33,958 --> 01:18:35,583
OK. I understand.

788
01:18:37,083 --> 01:18:37,916
I have to go.

789
01:18:46,916 --> 01:18:47,750
Mai.

790
01:18:50,750 --> 01:18:52,708
Gla chose to do what he did.

791
01:18:53,875 --> 01:18:56,458
Looking for answers
is putting you through pain.

792
01:19:00,708 --> 01:19:01,916
So can you stand it?

793
01:19:03,083 --> 01:19:04,750
Wondering and never knowing?

794
01:19:21,416 --> 01:19:22,250
Shit.

795
01:19:44,333 --> 01:19:45,333
How'd you get in?

796
01:19:45,416 --> 01:19:48,541
-Let me explain--
-About hiding Gla's laptop?

797
01:19:49,125 --> 01:19:50,500
-Mai--
-Explain to the cops.

798
01:19:50,583 --> 01:19:52,666
Mai, no! Hey! Mai, wait.

799
01:19:53,541 --> 01:19:55,083
Mai, listen to me first.

800
01:19:55,166 --> 01:19:58,458
I found his laptop
two days ago, in the trunk of my car.

801
01:20:00,250 --> 01:20:03,041
Earlier, I had to lie about not finding it

802
01:20:03,541 --> 01:20:07,958
because you made it sound like
the laptop was evidence. That scared me.

803
01:20:09,041 --> 01:20:11,208
I swear I knew nothing about it.

804
01:20:11,291 --> 01:20:13,125
I want to know Gla's story too.

805
01:20:15,750 --> 01:20:17,333
But his laptop is locked.

806
01:20:19,500 --> 01:20:20,458
I can't get in.

807
01:20:31,750 --> 01:20:33,916
Hey. We've tried for almost an hour.

808
01:20:34,750 --> 01:20:36,000
We've gotten nowhere.

809
01:20:36,750 --> 01:20:39,291
It'll be easier to hire an expert.

810
01:20:40,416 --> 01:20:42,083
I know this friend

811
01:20:42,625 --> 01:20:44,000
with IT qualifications.

812
01:20:44,791 --> 01:20:45,958
Should I ask them?

813
01:20:47,458 --> 01:20:48,458
Sure.

814
01:20:49,791 --> 01:20:52,791
Alright. I'll take it to my friend ASAP.

815
01:21:00,958 --> 01:21:02,500
You think I'm that stupid?

816
01:21:05,666 --> 01:21:06,541
You're lying.

817
01:21:08,125 --> 01:21:09,041
People like Gla

818
01:21:10,250 --> 01:21:12,375
never just suddenly kill themselves.

819
01:21:14,166 --> 01:21:15,416
I was his girlfriend.

820
01:21:16,416 --> 01:21:17,625
I knew him the best.

821
01:21:20,750 --> 01:21:22,708
I've been his friend for longer.

822
01:21:48,625 --> 01:21:49,791
So what now?

823
01:21:52,291 --> 01:21:54,125
Do I have to just accept it?

824
01:21:55,083 --> 01:21:57,625
That all this time
I didn't know Gla at all?

825
01:22:00,250 --> 01:22:01,666
I should have known

826
01:22:02,500 --> 01:22:04,166
